        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <p> It is the protection to defend internet connected devices from malicious attacks, hackers, spammers and cybercriminals It encompasses of strategies and measures put it in place to safeguard computers and networks but also invaluable data they store, defend against unauthorized access and threats lurking in the vast digital landscape The changing landscape of cybersecurity prevents ever-growing challenges for organizations worldwide. As we reach the 1990’s, many people started putting their personal information on the internet. Since people were doing this, it provided an opportunity for crime entities to steal that information and use that information as a source of income for them. This caused security threats to increase and firewalls and antivirus programmers, had to be put in place to protect the public. The early 2000’s crime companies started to spend a lot of funds on cyberattacks. Governments also started to give more serious sentences to those who are capable of hacking systems. From 2021 and onwards the cybersecurity industry will continue to grow at the speed of light. According to Statista, the global cybersecurity market size is predicted to increase to $345,4bn by the year 2026 :<a href="https://cybermagazine.com/cyber-security/history-cybersecurity" target="_blank">Learn more about Cybersecurity</a></p>
                <h6>Cybersecurity Applications</h6>
                <p>Notable applications used globally include Malwarebytes, Dynatrace, Sophos, and more, which safeguard businesses from cyber threats.</p>
